/-!
# Erdإ‘s 686, k=5: exact bipartite tangent cancellation

The product of the four tangent defects on a `2 x 2` crossing grid lies in
the integer ideal generated by the two-row product and the two-column
product.  This is the exact polynomial cancellation behind the finite
index-tuple resultant calculation; it is proved here uniformly, without an
enumeration or a trusted external algebra system.

After the four-crossing owner square is cancelled, the remaining row and
column cofactors are coprime and satisfy one explicit first-power owner
congruence.  Thus the square-level condition is not left as another raw
height bound.
-/

namespace Erdos686
